data.title: GalacticDNSMass: Bayesian inference determination of mass distribution of Galactic double neutron stars
data.name: GalacticDNSMass
data.description: How heavy are Neutron Stars in binary systems within our Galaxy? A demonstration of how bayesian inference and nested sampling allows us to explore the mass distributions of Galactic Double Neutron Star systems.

evidence: README mentions binaries/installers: "You can take a look at the [demo here](https://github.com/NicholasFarrow/GalacticDNSMass/blob/master/inferenceDemo.ipynb) or you can download the git repository with:"
"Here we provide code which performs Bayesian inference on a sample of 17 Galactic double neutron stars (DNS) in order to investigate their mass distribution."
"You can take a look at the demo here ... or you can download the git repository with: `git clone https://github.com/NicholasFarrow/GalacticDNSMass`."
